ct-ASRA CONTENT-TYPE ::= { TYPE ASRelationshipAttestation IDENTIFIED BY id-ct-ASRA }
ASRelationshipAttestation ::= SEQUENCE { version [0] INTEGER DEFAULT 0, SignerASID ASID, ASRAsubcategory subcategory, Relationships RelationshipASSet }
ASID ::= INTEGER (0..4294967295)
subcategory ::= OCTET STRING (SIZE (1))
RelationshipASSet ::= SEQUENCE (SIZE(1..MAX)) OF ASID
END

section.t:
ASRAsubcategory can have values 0 to 255. The values 1, 2, and 3 are assigned to represent ASRA1, ASRA2, and ASRA3, respectively. 
As explained in , ASRA1 means that the Relationships (see ) field contains ASIDs of only the customer ASes of the Signer AS; 
ASRA2 means that the Relationships field contains ASIDs of only the lateral peer ASes; 
ASRA3 means that the Relationships field contains the combined list of ASIDs of customer and lateral peer ASes.
Section 3 of   for details of registration requirements for ASRA1, ASRA2, and ASRA3.
